These two NEJM papers are both full results published on the same day. They are reported as a pooled analysis, not disaggregated, of this trial plus the heparin arms of two other ongoing adaptive trials. If those were completed, this would be a lot more complicated in our data but since they are not, and are therefore not going to be data points in our final analysis anyway, we can follow the precedent from the prone positioning trial and treat this as a pooled meta-result of the three trials with this one being fully reported in a journal article. So even though we couldn't disaggregate the data from this specific registration, we feel comfortable assigning the full results to the registration based on our data.
